1:10:23.510 --> 1:10:26.323
About me, about us.

1:10:31.448 --> 1:10:33.198
How is that possible?

1:10:34.670 --> 1:10:39.653
- I think, I think it's a kind of mercy.

1:10:43.410 --> 1:10:44.243
- And the baby?

1:10:46.394 --> 1:10:47.227
- That too.

1:10:49.840 --> 1:10:52.020
I think that's what it does.

1:10:52.020 --> 1:10:55.263
It doles out mercy, in its way.

1:10:58.705 --> 1:11:00.255
- That's a funny kind of mercy.

1:11:01.230 --> 1:11:03.600
- Its ways are not our ways.

1:11:03.600 --> 1:11:04.853
- You sound like my dad.

1:11:08.670 --> 1:11:09.990
- Maybe he's right.

1:11:09.990 --> 1:11:12.683
- No, no Joseph, that's not enough.

1:11:14.470 --> 1:11:15.383
What about us?

1:11:16.980 --> 1:11:18.253
What about our mercy?

1:11:20.410 --> 1:11:21.243
- Maybe...

1:11:24.560 --> 1:11:29.090
The mercy isn't for us
to receive this time.

1:11:29.090 --> 1:11:30.233
It's for us to give.

1:11:34.990 --> 1:11:36.543
- That's easy for you to say.

1:11:44.710 --> 1:11:46.510
They're never gonna believe us, huh.

1:11:47.770 --> 1:11:49.570
- It doesn't matter who believes it.

1:11:52.403 --> 1:11:54.248
I'm not even sure I believe it.

1:11:58.425 --> 1:12:00.400
But the truth is beyond belief.

1:12:17.040 --> 1:12:18.740
- That's easy for you to say.

1:12:26.990 --> 1:12:28.573
- So that's your story.

1:12:29.800 --> 1:12:31.300
That's what you're going with.

1:12:32.500 --> 1:12:34.100
- You said you wanted the truth,

1:12:36.290 --> 1:12:37.373
and this is it.

1:12:39.060 --> 1:12:42.003
- Yeah, it's just a little
hard to swallow, that's all.

1:12:46.810 --> 1:12:48.393
- It's not my fault.

1:12:53.510 --> 1:12:55.920
- We found Dennis Byrne, he's alive.

1:12:55.920 --> 1:12:58.580
We got him in the Medivac to
the hospital in Binghamton.

1:12:58.580 --> 1:12:59.660
- Status?

1:12:59.660 --> 1:13:02.000
- Rough, but he should pull through.

1:13:02.000 --> 1:13:05.280
- Okay thanks, notify the local Five-O.

1:13:05.280 --> 1:13:06.113
- Got it.

1:13:08.644 --> 1:13:11.311
(phone ringing)

1:13:14.880 --> 1:13:16.540
- Tell me you've got good news.

1:13:16.540 --> 1:13:19.956
- Well, I wouldn't call
it good news exactly.

1:13:19.956 --> 1:13:23.250
We found Dennis Bryne, and Alan Campbell,

1:13:23.250 --> 1:13:24.200
what's left of him.

1:13:25.330 --> 1:13:26.180
- Alright thanks.

1:13:26.180 --> 1:13:28.180
Let me know if you get anything else.

1:13:28.180 --> 1:13:29.070
- Copy that.

1:13:29.070 --> 1:13:31.793
- Sir, I think you need to see this.

1:13:33.556 --> 1:13:36.306
(birds chirping)

1:13:42.712 --> 1:13:47.712
- My dear, I believe you've
got one hell of a story for us.

1:13:52.940 --> 1:13:55.107
(panting)

1:14:08.605 --> 1:14:10.427
(whispering)

1:14:10.427 --> 1:14:12.760
- I'll handle the other one.

1:14:18.800 --> 1:14:19.800
- You're free to go.

1:14:25.530 --> 1:14:27.160
- Just like that.

1:14:27.160 --> 1:14:28.010
- Just like that.

1:14:40.750 --> 1:14:41.653
- What happened?

1:14:43.150 --> 1:14:44.830
- Well, I think you know
the answer to that better

1:14:44.830 --> 1:14:47.580
than we ever will, but we
have the answers we came for.

1:14:49.680 --> 1:14:51.753
- And that's enough?

1:14:53.380 --> 1:14:54.330
- It'll have to be.

1:15:05.300 --> 1:15:06.563
Have a nice life!

1:15:07.740 --> 1:15:11.150
- I grilled them over and over again.

1:15:11.150 --> 1:15:12.083
Grace too.

1:15:13.910 --> 1:15:15.173
Their stories match up.

1:15:16.990 --> 1:15:18.320
But there's not a shred of evidence

1:15:18.320 --> 1:15:19.830
to prove or disprove any of it,

1:15:19.830 --> 1:15:23.550
it's all this like,
bullshit about bright lights

1:15:23.550 --> 1:15:27.033
and demons, and I don't
know how to do that.

1:15:30.320 --> 1:15:31.170
- Bury it.

1:15:31.170 --> 1:15:34.620
- No Dad, I can't do that.

1:15:34.620 --> 1:15:35.453
- You heard me.

1:15:37.620 --> 1:15:39.020
The truth will not come out.

1:15:40.497 --> 1:15:41.597
It can never come out.

1:15:42.640 --> 1:15:43.563
You understand me?

1:15:51.930 --> 1:15:52.763
You know what?

1:15:55.110 --> 1:15:56.860
They died for what they believe in.

1:15:58.720 --> 1:15:59.763
Be proud of them.

1:16:01.800 --> 1:16:03.453
They've gone to a better place.

1:16:05.070 --> 1:16:06.190
You don't know how to do it,

1:16:06.190 --> 1:16:07.940
you don't know how to do it by now,

1:16:09.260 --> 1:16:13.780
say that they left fucking suicide notes

1:16:13.780 --> 1:16:15.660
and that the devil made 'em do it.

1:16:15.660 --> 1:16:18.783
Say that lightning struck
'em at the same moment.

1:16:19.880 --> 1:16:21.183
I don't give a shit.

1:16:23.110 --> 1:16:26.373
But do not question me, do not.

1:16:29.800 --> 1:16:32.143
- And Joseph Byrne, he
just gets to walk away?

1:16:33.800 --> 1:16:35.260
- Do it.

1:16:35.260 --> 1:16:37.660
- You think he's gonna
stay quiet with all this?

1:16:40.090 --> 1:16:42.290
- You will and I will, and in time,

1:16:42.290 --> 1:16:46.670
it'll all just go away, just like before.

1:16:57.300 --> 1:16:58.800
- You guys need anything else?

1:17:01.600 --> 1:17:02.650
- I think we're good.

1:17:11.150 --> 1:17:13.200
So you believe they're telling the truth?

1:17:14.720 --> 1:17:16.350
- They believe it.

1:17:16.350 --> 1:17:18.050
That's good enough for us for now.

1:17:19.460 --> 1:17:20.933
- What about Carl Campbell?

1:17:22.950 --> 1:17:24.690
- He'll turn up or he won't.

1:17:24.690 --> 1:17:26.960
I'm sure the local yokels
will pin the rest on him.

1:17:26.960 --> 1:17:28.060
- Or they won't.

1:17:28.060 --> 1:17:31.023
The saw is family, as they say
in situations such as this.

1:17:31.900 --> 1:17:33.650
- Either way, it's not our problem.

1:17:34.970 --> 1:17:37.350
Let the little people deal with it.

